63. Difference Between is and ==
x = [1, 2, 3]
y = [1, 2, 3]
z = x

print("x == y :", x == y)  # compares values
print("x is y :", x is y)  # compares memory location

print("x == z :", x == z)
print("x is z :", x is z)

output:
x == y : True
x is y : False
x == z : True
x is z : True


